'''Ali Akdemir''' (born June 3, 1963 in [[Sivas]]) is a [[Turkish people|Turkish]] University Professor for Management and former Rector of the [[Çanakkale Onsekiz Mart University]] (Gallipoli).<ref>{{cite news|title=Çanakkale 18 Mart Üniversitesi'nden insanlık ayıbı |url=http://www.zaman.com.tr/haber.do?haberno=687743 |work=[[Zaman (newspaper)|Zaman]] |date=10 May 2008 |accessdate=15 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229132939/http://www.zaman.com.tr/haber.do?haberno=687743 |archivedate=29 February 2012 }}</ref> He is the former Dean of the Biga Faculty Of Economics and Administrative Sciences (BIIBF) at Çanakkale Onsekiz Mart University (Gallipoli). His main research area is on management and leadership issues, has some several articles and presentations.
Prof. Akdemir was Chairman of the [[World Universities Congress]] in Canakkale and is editor of the [[Journal of Administrative Sciences]].
