{{Short description|Nepalese politician}} {{Infobox officeholder |name= Rajeev Bikram Shah |native_name= राजीव विक्रम शाह |image= |office = Member of [[Legislature Parliament of Nepal]] from [[Jajarkot District|Jajarkot]] Constituency No. 2 |predecessor = [[Bhakta Bahadur Shah]] |successor = [[Shakti Bahadur Basnet]] (merged two Constituencies of Jajarkot in 2017) |term_start = January 2014 |term_end = December 2017 |party= [[Nepali Congress]] |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1968|04|08|df=y}} |birth_place= [[Kathmandu]] |father = |mother = }}
'''Rajeev Bikram Shah''' ({{lang-ne|राजीव विक्रम शाह}}) is a Nepalese politician. He was elected as a member of Constituent Assembly from [[Nepalese Constituent Assembly election, 2013|second Constitutional Assembly election]] held on 19 November 2013 from [[Jajarkot District|Jajarkot]] Constituency No. 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nepalconsulate.net.au/nc-youth-leader-and-ca-member-rajeev-bikram-shah-welcomed-in-melbourne/|title=NC Youth Leader and CA Member Rajeev Bikram Shah welcomed in Melbourne |author= |date= |work= |publisher= Consulate General of Nepal Victoria, Australia |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> He is the president of [[Nepal Amateur Athletic Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nocnepal.org.np/nepal-amateur-athletics-association |title=Nepal Amateur Athletics Association |author= |date= |work= |publisher= Nepal Olympic Committee|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/sports-figures-contesting-elections/attachment/nepal-athletics-association-president-rajeev-bikram-shah/ |title=Nepal Athletics Association President Rajeev Bikram Shah|author= |date= |work= |publisher=The Himalayan Times |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> In [[Nepalese legislative election, 2017]] he was candidate from [[Jajarkot District|Jajarkot]] constituency No. 1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/basnet-shah-contesting-jajarkot-1/ |title= Basnet, Shah contesting from Jajarkot-1|author= |date= |work= |publisher= The Himalayan Times|accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>
